        "id": 1099352
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-08-03T23:52:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Should the entry for puid be removed from m_procOwnedEGLImages if this erase reduces the size of the set to zero?  Or are you relying on cleanup eventually doing that when the process dies.  I don\u0027t know if you could have a large number of guest processes that create images, then destroy them, but continue running for a long time.\n\nI think it would be safer/cleaner to do the cleanup here when possible, just to avoid thinking about it further.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1088,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 1088,
        "endChar": 44
      },
